-- UAE Port Fujairah Stops Ships From Anchoring in Adjacent Waters
-- B y   A l a r i c   N i g h t i n g a l e
-- 2013-03-15T07:29:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-15/uae-port-fujairah-stops-ships-from-anchoring-in-adjacent-waters.html
The Port of Fujairah in the United
Arab Emirates stopped ships from anchoring in adjacent
territorial waters, according to a notice to port agents
published by Inchcape Shipping Services.  “Considering the safety, security and environmental
issues, vessels anchoring adjacent to Fujairah territorial
waters is strictly prohibited with immediate effect,” according
to the  port notice,  republished on Inchcape’s website. Ships are
still allowed to navigate the area.  To contact the reporter on this story:
